<task id="task_u5b_dlw_pm">
    <title>Create a customization plugin <ph outputclass="quiet">(an example)</ph></title>
    <shortdesc>In order to develop a new theme, you need to develop a customization plugin.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq>The DITA for Publishers html5 plugin is required. This plugin must be in a folder
            named <filepath>net.sourceforge.dita4publishers.html5</filepath>.</prereq>
        <context>
            <p>In this tutorial, we will do a minimal implementation of the <xref
                    keyref="foundation"/> using the html5 plugin.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Download and install the <xref keyref="d4p-utils"
                        >net.sourceforge.dita4publishers.utils</xref> plugin.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Create a customization plugin.</cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <p>Using the command line, run:</p>
                    <codeblock>
                        <data-about>
                            <data name="language" value="bash"/>
                        </data-about>
 ant -f plugins/net.sourceforge.dita4publishers.utils
                    </codeblock>
                    <p>Choose the following options: <ul>
                            <li>Type choice 1, then press enter,</li>
                            <li><msgph>Plugin's domain:</msgph> Leave as is and press
                                    <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</li>
                            <li><msgph>Plugin's name:</msgph> Leave as is and press
                                    <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</li>
                            <li><msgph>Plugin's transtype:</msgph> Type <q>foundation</q> and press
                                    <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</li>
                            <li><msgph>Plugin's theme:</msgph> Leave as is and press
                                    <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </stepxmp>
                <stepresult> The utility will create a complete customization plugin. </stepresult>
            </step>
            
            <step>
                <cmd>Run the integrator</cmd>
                <info>
                    <codeblock>
                         <data-about>
                            <data name="language" value="bash"/>
                        </data-about>
 ant -f integrator.xml
                    </codeblock>
                </info>
            </step>
            
            <step importance="optional">
                <cmd>To test the new transtype, build the sample documentation. </cmd>
                <info>
                    <codeblock>
                        <data-about>
                            <data name="language" value="bash"/>
                        </data-about>
 ant -Dargs.input=samples/sequence.ditamap -Doutput.dir=out/garage -Dtranstype=foundation
                    </codeblock>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
